definition.value: Salicylaldehyde imine with a tosyl (toluene-p-sulfonyl) group bonded to the imine N atom.

Any member of the cephamycin sub-group of cephem antibiotics, differing from cephalosporins in possessing a methoxy group at the 7alpha-position of the cephem nucleus, and in being resistant to beta-lactamase.
A 1-O-alkyl-2-O-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine where the alkyl group is specified as hexadecyl.
A ketoaldohexose compound consisting of a pyranose ring with keto groups at the 2- and 3-positions.
The 2,3-didehydro derivative of D-glucose.
A diketide with a pentanoic acid structure substituted at the alpha and beta positions by methyl and hydroxy groups respectively.
A dipeptide consisting of an L-aspartyl residue attached to L-arginine via the beta-carboxy group.
A primary amine of general formula RCH2CH2NH2 where R represents an aryl moiety.
A polyprenylnaphthohydroquinone that is naphthalene-1,4-diol having a polyprenyl substituent of unspecified chain-length at the 2-position.
An angiotensin compound consisting of the linear heptapeptide sequence L-Asp-L-Arg-L-Val-L-Tyr-L-Ile-L-His-L-Pro.
Amide formed between amoxicillin and benzylamine.
A penicillin-derived group formed from nucleophilic cleavage of the beta-lactam ring of 6-aminopenicillanic acid.
Amide formed between 6-aminopenicillanic acid and benzylamine.
A phenol that is the N-(4-hydroxyphenyl) derivative of glycine. Synthesised by reaction of p-aminophenol with chloracetic acid, it is used as a photographic developing agent.
1,3-Thiazolidine substituted with methyl groups at C-2, -5 and -5 and with a carboxy group at C-4, representing the thiazolidine ring of a generalised penicillin structure.

A cephalosporin with  acetoxymethyl and 2(pyridin-4-ylsulfanyl)acetamido substituents at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton. It is used (as its sodium salt) as an antibiotic, being effective against gram-negative and gram-positive organisms.
Ferrocene substituted on one of the cyclopentadienyl rings by a vinyl group.
A polycyclic compound comprising a 5-hydroxy-4H-chromen-4-one core with 3-sulfooxyphenyl and 6-gulonate substituents; which can act as a non-peptide antigen.
The conjugate base of 6-O-{5-hydroxy-4-oxo-3-[2-(sulfooxy)phenyl]-4H-chromen-6-yl}-L-gulonic acid.

A compound comprising a 2-(5-hydroxy-4-oxo-4H-chromen-3-yl)phenyl sulfate core with a 9-1-(1-carboxy-2-oxoethoxy)-2-oxoethanolate substituent; a product of 6-O-{5-hydroxy-4-oxo-3-[2-(sulfooxy)phenyl]-4H-chromen-6-yl}-L-gulonic acid oxidation.
The product of desulfonating 6-O-{5-hydroxy-4-oxo-3-[2-(sulfooxy)phenyl]-4H-chromen-6-yl}-L-gulonic acid.
The conjugate base of 6-O-[5-hydroxy-3-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-4-oxo-4H-chromen-6-yl]-L-gulonic acid.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having adenine as the nucleobase and a lipoyl group attached to one of the phosphate OH groups.
The conjugate base of genistin 4',6''-disulfate.
The conjugate base of genistein 4',7-disulfate.
A bisulfonated derivative of genistein.
An anthocyanin cation consisting of delphinidin with two beta-D-glucosyl residues attached to the 3- and 5-hydroxy groups.
An anthocyanin cation consisting of delphinidin with three beta-D-glucosyl residues attached to the 3-, 3'- and 5-hydroxy groups.
A bisulfonated derivative of genistin.
A pyridine nucleoside consisting of 1,4-dihydronicotinamide with a beta-D-ribofuranosyl moiety at the 1-position.
An acyl group formed from nucleophilic cleavage of the beta-lactam ring of sulbenicillin.
An acyl group derived from trimellitic acid by the removal of a hydroxy substituent from the carboxy group at C-4.
A cyclic dicarboxylic anhydride that is the cyclic anhydride of methylhexahydrophthalic acid.
A ketoaldohexose compound consisting of a pyranose ring with keto groups at the 3- and 4-positions.
The 3,4-didehydro derivative of D-glucose.
A beta-D-glucoside having a beta-D-apiosyl residue at the 2-position and an isoflavon-7-yl moiety at the anomeric position.
A hydroxyisoflavone compound having a hydroxy group at the 7-position.
A cyclic dicarboxylic anhydride that is the cyclic anhydride of methyltetrahydrophthalic acid.
A 7-[beta-D-apiofuranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyloxy]isoflavone having methoxy substituents at the 6- and 2'-positions and a methylenedioxy moiety at the 4'- and 5'-positions.
An acyl group formed from nucleophilic cleavage of the beta-lactam ring of carbenicillin.
An acetamide compound of general formula RCH2CH2NHC(=O)CH3 where R represents an aryl moiety.
A monocarboxylic acid amide formed by nucleophilic ring cleavage of the beta-lactam ring of amoxicillin by butylamine.
An N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group having beta-configuration at its point of attachment.
An amide formed between benzylpenicillin and butylamine.
An amide formed between ampicillin and butylamine.
An N-acyl homoserine lactone that has L configuration.
